{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id797cb132-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1471"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1471"},"text":"§ 1471.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definitions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For the purpose of this Act—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id797cb133-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1471/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “Commission” means the Consumer Product Safety Commission.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id797cb134-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1471/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The term “household substance” means any substance which is customarily produced or distributed for sale for consumption or use, or customarily stored, by individuals in or about the household and which is—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id797cb135-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1471/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a hazardous substance as that term is defined in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s1261/f"},"text":"section 1261(f) of this title","children":[],"tail":";"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id797cb136-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1471/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a food, drug, or cosmetic as those terms are defined in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s321"},"text":"section 321 of title 21","children":[],"tail":"; or"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id797cb137-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1471/2/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a substance intended for use as fuel when stored in a portable container and used in the heating, cooking, or refrigeration system of a house.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id797cb138-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1471/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The term “package” means the immediate container or wrapping in which any household substance is contained for consumption, use, or storage by individuals in or about the household, and, for purposes of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s1473/a/2"},"text":"section 1473(a)(2) of this title","children":[],"tail":", also means any outer container or wrapping used in the retail display of any such substance to consumers. Such term does not include—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id797cb139-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1471/3/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" any shipping container or wrapping used solely for the transportation of any household substance in bulk or in quantity to manufacturers, packers, or processors, or to wholesale or retail distributors thereof, or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id797cb13a-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1471/3/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" any shipping container or outer wrapping used by retailers to ship or deliver any household substance to consumers unless it is the only such container or wrapping.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id797cb13b-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1471/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “special packaging” means packaging that is designed or constructed to be significantly difficult for children under five years of age to open or obtain a toxic or harmful amount of the substance contained therein within a reasonable time and not difficult for normal adults to use properly, but does not mean packaging which all such children cannot open or obtain a toxic or harmful amount within a reasonable time.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id797cb13c-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1471/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “labeling” means all labels and other written, printed, or graphic matter (A) upon any household substance or its package, or (B) accompanying such substance.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id797cb13d-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/601/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–601, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-12-30"},"text":"Dec. 30, 1970","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/1670"},"text":"84 Stat. 1670","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/516/s3/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–516, § 3(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1972-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1972","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/86/998"},"text":"86 Stat. 998","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/573/s30/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–573, § 30(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1972-10-27"},"text":"Oct. 27, 1972","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/86/1231"},"text":"86 Stat. 1231","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/284/s3/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–284, § 3(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-05-11"},"text":"May 11, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/503"},"text":"90 Stat. 503","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id797cb13e-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id797cb13f-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id797cb140-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This Act, referred to in text, means ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/601"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–601","children":[],"tail":" which enacted this chapter, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s136/z/2/i"},"text":"section 136(z)(2)(i) of Title 7","children":[],"tail":", Agriculture, and sections 343(n), 352(p), and 362(f) of Title 21, Food and Drugs, amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s1261/p"},"text":"section 1261(p) of this title","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s353/b/2"},"text":"section 353(b)(2) of Title 21","children":[],"tail":", and enacted provisions set out as a note under this section. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note below and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id797cb141-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1976—Par. (2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/284"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–284","children":[],"tail":" struck out subpar. (B) which included pesticide as defined in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s136/u"},"text":"section 136(u) of Title 7","children":[],"tail":" within meaning of “household substance”, and redesignated subpars. (C) and (D) as (B) and (C), respectively."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1972—Par. (2)(B). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/516"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–516","children":[],"tail":" substituted “a pesticide” for “an economic poison”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id797cb142-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id797cb143-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1972 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For effective date of amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/516"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–516","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/516/s4"},"text":"section 4 of Pub. L. 92–516","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s136"},"text":"section 136 of Title 7","children":[],"tail":", Agriculture."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"id797cb144-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/601/s8"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–601, § 8","children":[],"tail":", formerly § 9, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-12-30"},"text":"Dec. 30, 1970","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/1674"},"text":"84 Stat. 1674","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/573/s30/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–573, § 30(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1972-10-27"},"text":"Oct. 27, 1972","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/86/1231"},"text":"86 Stat. 1231","children":[],"tail":", and renumbered by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/35/tXII/s1205/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–35, title XII, § 1205(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-08-13"},"text":"Aug. 13, 1981","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/95/716"},"text":"95 Stat. 716","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/97/35/tXII/s1205/c"},"text":"“This Act [see Short Title note set out below] shall take effect on the date of its enactment [","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-12-30"},"text":"Dec. 30, 1970","children":[],"tail":"]. Each regulation establishing a special packaging standard shall specify the date such standard is to take effect which date shall not be sooner than one hundred and eighty days or later than one year from the date such regulation is final, unless the Commission, for good cause found, determines that an earlier effective date is in the public interest and publishes in the Federal Register his reason for such finding, in which case such earlier date shall apply. No such standard shall be effective as to household substances subject to this Act packaged prior to the effective date of such final regulation.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitleOfAmendment","id":"id797cb145-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title of 2016 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/116/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–116, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2016-01-28"},"text":"Jan. 28, 2016","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/130/3"},"text":"130 Stat. 3","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/114/116/s1"},"text":"“This Act [enacting ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s1472a"},"text":"section 1472a of this title","children":[],"tail":" and provisions set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s1472a"},"text":"section 1472a of this title","children":[],"tail":"] may be cited as the ‘Child Nicotine Poisoning Prevention Act of 2015’.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitle","id":"id797cb146-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/601/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–601, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-12-30"},"text":"Dec. 30, 1970","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/1670"},"text":"84 Stat. 1670","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/91/601/s1"},"text":"“This Act [enacting this chapter, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s135/z/2/i"},"text":"section 135(z)(2)(i) of Title 7","children":[],"tail":", Agriculture, and sections 343(n), 352(p), and 362(f) of Title 21, Food and Drugs, amending "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s1261/p"},"text":"section 1261(p) of this title","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s353/b/2"},"text":"section 353(b)(2) of Title 21","children":[],"tail":", and enacting provisions set out as a note under this section] may be cited as the ‘Poison Prevention Packaging Act of 1970’.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"id797cb147-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“Commission” substituted for “Secretary” and “Consumer Product Safety Commission” substituted for “Secretary of Health, Education, and Welfare” in par. (1) pursuant to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/573/s30/a"},"text":"section 30(a) of Pub. L. 92–573","children":[],"tail":", which is classified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s2079/a"},"text":"section 2079(a) of this title","children":[],"tail":" and which transferred functions of Secretary of Health, Education, and Welfare under this chapter to Consumer Product Safety Commission."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
